  "why": "The paper enforces semantic-consistency / naturalness checks on each mutation step (using an is_valid check and a small set of realistic transformation operators) and reports that NLC-guided mutations produce more natural-looking outputs (measured by IS/FID). However, the mutation acceptance test is performed between the newly mutated input and the currently sampled seed (ŝ ← t(s); is_valid(ŝ,s)), i.e., similarity is enforced relative to the most recent mutant rather than the original seed, and the paper gives no mechanism that constrains cumulative distortion relative to the original seed across multiple iterations. Thus plausibility is enforced between successive steps but the design does not account for drift accumulation across iterations.",
